TITLE: Querying Multiple Aggregations with TopN in Apache Druid
DESCRIPTION: A TopN query that aggregates multiple line item metrics (tax, discount, price, quantity) filtered by specific order keys. The query includes sum aggregations for numeric fields, a count aggregation, and uses an OR filter to match specific order keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.2-incubating/querying/topnquery.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "aggregations": [
             {
                 "fieldName": "L_TAX_doubleSum",
                 "name": "L_TAX_",
                 "type": "doubleSum"
             },
             {
                 "fieldName": "L_DISCOUNT_doubleSum",
                 "name": "L_DISCOUNT_",
                 "type": "doubleSum"
             },
             {
                 "fieldName": "L_EXTENDEDPRICE_doubleSum",
                 "name": "L_EXTENDEDPRICE_",
                 "type": "doubleSum"
             },
             {
                 "fieldName": "L_QUANTITY_longSum",
                 "name": "L_QUANTITY_",
                 "type": "longSum"
             },
             {
                 "name": "count",
                 "type": "count"
             }
    ],
    "dataSource": "tpch_year",
    "dimension":"l_orderkey",
    "filter": {
        "fields": [
            {
                "dimension": "l_orderkey",
                "type": "selector",
                "value": "103136"
            },
            {
                "dimension": "l_orderkey",
                "type": "selector",
                "value": "1648672"
            }
        ],
        "type": "or"
    },
    "granularity": "all",
    "intervals": [
        "1900-01-09T00:00:00.000Z/2992-01-10T00:00:00.000Z"
    ],
    "metric": "L_QUANTITY_",
    "queryType": "topN",
    "threshold": 2
}
```

