TITLE: Querying Segment Statistics using SQL in Apache Druid
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query retrieves statistics about published segments in a specified dataSource, including average number of rows, average size, and total size. It helps identify segments that may need compaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.1-incubating/operations/segment-optimization.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT
  "start",
  "end",
  version,
  COUNT(*) AS num_segments,
  AVG("num_rows") AS avg_num_rows,
  SUM("num_rows") AS total_num_rows,
  AVG("size") AS avg_size,
  SUM("size") AS total_size
FROM
  sys.segments A
WHERE
  datasource = 'your_dataSource' AND
  is_published = 1
GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
ORDER BY 1, 2, 3 DESC;
```

