TITLE: Configuring JavaScript ParseSpec in Druid Ingestion
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure a JavaScript parser in Druid's ingestion specification. The example includes a custom parsing function that splits a string by hyphen and returns a key-value object. The configuration also specifies timestamp and dimension specifications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.0-incubating/ingestion/data-formats.md#2025-04-09_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
  "parseSpec":{
    "format" : "javascript",
    "timestampSpec" : {
      "column" : "timestamp"
    },        
    "dimensionsSpec" : {
      "dimensions" : ["page","language","user","unpatrolled","newPage","robot","anonymous","namespace","continent","country","region","city"]
    },
    "function" : "function(str) { var parts = str.split(\"-\"); return { one: parts[0], two: parts[1] } }"
  }
```

