TITLE: Aggregating Segment Metrics by Datasource
DESCRIPTION: SQL query to calculate total size, average size, average number of rows and segment count grouped by datasource.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.15.1-incubating/querying/sql.md#2025-04-09_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT
    datasource,
    SUM("size") AS total_size,
    CASE WHEN SUM("size") = 0 THEN 0 ELSE SUM("size") / (COUNT(*) FILTER(WHERE "size" > 0)) END AS avg_size,
    CASE WHEN SUM(num_rows) = 0 THEN 0 ELSE SUM("num_rows") / (COUNT(*) FILTER(WHERE num_rows > 0)) END AS avg_num_rows,
    COUNT(*) AS num_segments
FROM sys.segments
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 2 DESC
```

