TITLE: Querying System Schema for Segment Metrics in Apache Druid SQL
DESCRIPTION: SQL query that retrieves metrics about published segments from the system schema, including average row count, segment size, and total counts. This query helps determine if segments need compaction by analyzing their current characteristics.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.2-incubating/operations/segment-optimization.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT
  "start",
  "end",
  version,
  COUNT(*) AS num_segments,
  AVG("num_rows") AS avg_num_rows,
  SUM("num_rows") AS total_num_rows,
  AVG("size") AS avg_size,
  SUM("size") AS total_size
FROM
  sys.segments A
WHERE
  datasource = 'your_dataSource' AND
  is_published = 1
GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
ORDER BY 1, 2, 3 DESC;
```

