TITLE: Configuring Parquet Parser with TimeAndDims ParseSpec in Druid
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration for ingesting Parquet files using the 'parquet' parser type with a timeAndDims parseSpec. This configuration explicitly defines dimensions without using field discovery or flattening.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.15.1-incubating/development/extensions-core/parquet.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type": "index_hadoop",
  "spec": {
    "ioConfig": {
      "type": "hadoop",
      "inputSpec": {
        "type": "static",
        "inputFormat": "org.apache.druid.data.input.parquet.DruidParquetInputFormat",
        "paths": "path/to/file.parquet"
      },
      ...
    },
    "dataSchema": {
      "dataSource": "example",
      "parser": {
        "type": "parquet",
        "parseSpec": {
          "format": "timeAndDims",
          "timestampSpec": {
            "column": "timestamp",
            "format": "auto"
          },
          "dimensionsSpec": {
            "dimensions": [
              "dim1",
              "dim2",
              "dim3",
              "listDim"
            ],
            "dimensionExclusions": [],
            "spatialDimensions": []
          }
        }
      },
      ...
    },
    "tuningConfig": <hadoop-tuning-config>
  }
}
```

