TITLE: Full Serialization Format for Histograms in Apache Druid
DESCRIPTION: Defines the byte-level structure for fully serializing histogram data, including version, encoding mode, limits, bucket counts, and outlier handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.15.0-incubating/development/extensions-core/approximate-histograms.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
byte: serialization version, must be 0x01
byte: encoding mode, 0x01 for full
double: lowerLimit
double: upperLimit
int: numBuckets
byte: outlier handling mode (0x00 for `ignore`, 0x01 for `overflow`, and 0x02 for `clip`)
long: count, total number of values contained in the histogram, excluding outliers
long: lowerOutlierCount
long: upperOutlierCount
long: missingValueCount
double: max
double: min
array of longs: bucket counts for the histogram
```

