TITLE: Calculating Rollup Ratio with Druid SQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query calculates the rollup ratio of a datasource by comparing the number of rows in Druid with the number of ingested events. It uses the SUM of event_count divided by the COUNT of rows, multiplied by 1.0 to ensure decimal division.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.1-incubating/ingestion/schema-design.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
SELECT SUM("event_count") / COUNT(*) * 1.0 FROM datasource
```

