TITLE: Configuring Inline Lookup Extraction Function with Map in Druid
DESCRIPTION: An example of an inline lookup extraction function that specifies a mapping directly in the query rather than referencing a registered lookup. This example retains missing values and marks the lookup as injective.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.2-incubating/querying/dimensionspecs.md#2025-04-09_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "type":"lookup",
  "lookup":{
    "type":"map",
    "map":{"foo":"bar", "baz":"bat"}
  },
  "retainMissingValue":true,
  "injective":true
}
```

