TITLE: Submitting Overlord Dynamic Configuration in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON object can be submitted to the Overlord via a POST request to configure worker behavior dynamically. It includes settings for worker selection strategy and autoscaling configuration for EC2.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.13.0-incubating/configuration/index.md#2025-04-09_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "selectStrategy": {
    "type": "fillCapacity",
    "affinityConfig": {
      "affinity": {
        "datasource1": ["host1:port", "host2:port"],
        "datasource2": ["host3:port"]
      }
    }
  },
  "autoScaler": {
    "type": "ec2",
    "minNumWorkers": 2,
    "maxNumWorkers": 12,
    "envConfig": {
      "availabilityZone": "us-east-1a",
      "nodeData": {
        "amiId": "${AMI}",
        "instanceType": "c3.8xlarge",
        "minInstances": 1,
        "maxInstances": 1,
        "securityGroupIds": ["${IDs}"],
        "keyName": "${KEY_NAME}"
      },
      "userData": {
        "impl": "string",
        "data": "${SCRIPT_COMMAND}",
        "versionReplacementString": ":VERSION:",
        "version": null
      }
    }
  }
}
```

