TITLE: Configuring log4j2 XML for Druid Logging
DESCRIPTION: Example log4j2.xml configuration file for Druid that sets up console logging with timestamp patterns and configurable log levels. Includes optional HTTP request logging configuration that can be uncommented.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.13.0-incubating/configuration/logging.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: xml
CODE:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<Configuration status="WARN">
  <Appenders>
    <Console name="Console" target="SYSTEM_OUT">
      <PatternLayout pattern="%d{ISO8601} %p [%t] %c - %m%n"/>
    </Console>
  </Appenders>
  <Loggers>
    <Root level="info">
      <AppenderRef ref="Console"/>
    </Root>

    <!-- Uncomment to enable logging of all HTTP requests
    <Logger name="org.apache.druid.jetty.RequestLog" additivity="false" level="DEBUG">
        <AppenderRef ref="Console"/>
    </Logger>
    -->
  </Loggers>
</Configuration>
```

