TITLE: Configuring Kafka Eight Firehose in Apache Druid
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates how to configure the Kafka Eight Firehose in Apache Druid. It specifies consumer properties for connecting to Zookeeper, setting up the consumer group, and defining message handling parameters. The 'feed' property specifies the Kafka topic to consume from.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.14.1-incubating/development/extensions-core/kafka-eight-firehose.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
"firehose": {
  "type": "kafka-0.8",
  "consumerProps": {
    "zookeeper.connect": "localhost:2181",
    "zookeeper.connection.timeout.ms" : "15000",
    "zookeeper.session.timeout.ms" : "15000",
    "zookeeper.sync.time.ms" : "5000",
    "group.id": "druid-example",
    "fetch.message.max.bytes" : "1048586",
    "auto.offset.reset": "largest",
    "auto.commit.enable": "false"
  },
  "feed": "wikipedia"
}
```

