TITLE: GroupBy Query with Filtered DimensionSpec for Multi-value Dimensions
DESCRIPTION: Example of a GroupBy query with both a selector filter and a filtered dimension specification. This approach filters the rows first, then limits the dimension values to only 't3', providing more targeted results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.15.1-incubating/querying/multi-value-dimensions.md#2025-04-09_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "queryType": "groupBy",
  "dataSource": "test",
  "intervals": [
    "1970-01-01T00:00:00.000Z/3000-01-01T00:00:00.000Z"
  ],
  "filter": {
    "type": "selector",
    "dimension": "tags",
    "value": "t3"
  },
  "granularity": {
    "type": "all"
  },
  "dimensions": [
    {
      "type": "listFiltered",
      "delegate": {
        "type": "default",
        "dimension": "tags",
        "outputName": "tags"
      },
      "values": ["t3"]
    }
  ],
  "aggregations": [
    {
      "type": "count",
      "name": "count"
    }
  ]
}
```

