TITLE: Running insert-segment-to-db Tool with MySQL and HDFS for Wikipedia Segments
DESCRIPTION: Command to run the insert-segment-to-db tool with MySQL as metadata storage and HDFS as deep storage. The example loads segments from a Wikipedia dataset stored in HDFS, configuring necessary connection parameters and loading the required MySQL and HDFS storage extensions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.13.0-incubating/operations/insert-segment-to-db.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
java 
-Ddruid.metadata.storage.type=mysql 
-Ddruid.metadata.storage.connector.connectURI=jdbc\:mysql\://localhost\:3306/druid 
-Ddruid.metadata.storage.connector.user=druid 
-Ddruid.metadata.storage.connector.password=diurd 
-Ddruid.extensions.loadList=[\"mysql-metadata-storage\",\"druid-hdfs-storage\"] 
-Ddruid.storage.type=hdfs
-cp $DRUID_CLASSPATH 
org.apache.druid.cli.Main tools insert-segment-to-db --workingDir hdfs://host:port//druid/storage/wikipedia --updateDescriptor true
```

