TITLE: ResetCluster Tool Help Output
DESCRIPTION: Complete help documentation output showing the tool's name, synopsis, and available options for cleaning up different components of the Druid cluster state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apache/druid-website/blob/asf-site/docs/0.15.1-incubating/operations/reset-cluster.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
NAME
        druid tools reset-cluster - Cleanup all persisted state from metadata
        and deep storage.

SYNOPSIS
        druid tools reset-cluster [--all] [--hadoopWorkingPath]
                [--metadataStore] [--segmentFiles] [--taskLogs]

OPTIONS
        --all
            delete all state stored in metadata and deep storage

        --hadoopWorkingPath
            delete hadoopWorkingPath

        --metadataStore
            delete all records in metadata storage

        --segmentFiles
            delete all segment files from deep storage

        --taskLogs
            delete all tasklogs
```

